<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="297" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="0.[136,1452,1479,1646]" pageId="0" pageNumber="297">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,267,1479,1501]" pageId="0" pageNumber="297">Diagnosis:—</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="X. Y. Huang, Y. D. Peng &amp; D. X. Nong" authorityYear="2022" box="[267,444,1480,1501]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Aspidistra" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="0" pageNumber="297" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="saccata">
<emphasis box="[267,444,1480,1501]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="297">Aspidistra saccata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is morphologically similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[733,836,1480,1501]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Aspidistra" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="0" pageNumber="297" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="globosa">
<emphasis box="[733,836,1480,1501]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="297">A. globosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in erect stem, but clearly distinguished by its smaller leaf blade, depressed-globose flower shape, perigone tube with 6 prominent saccular-like keels, cylindric style, slightly enlarged stigma, ca. 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="0" pageNumber="297" unit="mm" value="2.5" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.0">2–3 mm</quantity>
across and smooth berry.
</paragraph>
