Aver., Vuong, T.N. Bon &amp; V.S. Dang
</taxonomicName>
in 
<bibRefCitation author="Averyanov, L. V. &amp; Truong, B. V. &amp; Trinh, B. N. &amp; Dang, S. V. &amp; Bui, V. H. &amp; Le, T. A. &amp; Nguyen, T. H. A. &amp; Do, T. T. H. &amp; Nguyen, C. V. &amp; Maisak, T. V. &amp; Nguyen, K. S. &amp; Tillich, H. - J." box="[423,708,483,507]" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" pagination="1 - 6" refId="ref1752" refString="Averyanov, L. V., Truong, B. V., Trinh, B. N., Dang, S. V., Bui, V. H., Le, T. A., Nguyen, T. H. A., Do, T. T. H., Nguyen, C. V., Maisak, T. V., Nguyen, K. S. &amp; Tillich, H. - J. (2021) Aspidistra peltata, Convallariaceae (Asparagaceae s. l.) a new species from northern Vietnam. Nordic Journal of Botany 39 (6): 1 - 6. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / njb. 03090" type="journal article" year="2021">
Averyanov 
<emphasis box="[549,605,483,507]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">et al.</emphasis>
(2021:2)
</bibRefCitation>
. Among them 
<taxonomicName box="[871,969,483,507]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Aspidistra" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="erecta">
<emphasis box="[871,969,483,507]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">A. erecta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[1026,1132,483,507]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Aspidistra" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nikolai">
<emphasis box="[1026,1132,483,507]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">A. nikolai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are really tall herbs with the stem about 
<quantity box="[260,301,519,543]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" unit="m" value="1.0">1 m</quantity>
high, while stems of 
<taxonomicName box="[533,611,519,543]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Aspidistra" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="locii">
<emphasis box="[533,611,519,543]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">A. locii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis box="[625,970,519,543]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tillich" authorityYear="2005" box="[625,746,519,543]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Aspidistra" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lateralis">A. lateralis</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Averyanov &amp; Tillich" authorityYear="2014" box="[757,870,519,543]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Aspidistra" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="khangii">A. khangii</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Averyanov &amp; Tillich" authorityYear="2014" box="[881,970,519,543]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Aspidistra" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lubae">A. lubae</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[1023,1194,519,543]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Aspidistra" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="brachypetala">
<emphasis box="[1023,1194,519,543]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">A. brachypetala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
do not exceed 
<quantity box="[1357,1424,519,543]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" unit="cm" value="10.0">10 cm</quantity>
in height. However, these species significantly differ from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="X. Y. Huang, Y. D. Peng &amp; D. X. Nong" authorityYear="2022" box="[729,838,555,579]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Aspidistra" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="saccata">
<emphasis box="[729,838,555,579]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">A. saccata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in structure of flower. The new species most resembles 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Aspidistra" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="globosa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">A. globosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[270,372,591,615]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Aspidistra" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="peltata">
<emphasis box="[270,372,591,615]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">A. peltata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in stem, but differs in leaves attachment, smaller leaf blade, depressed-globose flower shape, perigone tube with 6 prominent saccular-like keels, cylindric style and slightly enlarged stigma, ca. 
<quantity box="[1098,1185,627,651]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" unit="mm" value="2.5" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.0">2–3 mm</quantity>
across. It also resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="S. Z. He, W. F. Xu &amp; Q. W. Sun" authorityName="S. Z. He, W. F. Xu &amp; Q. W. Sun" box="[136,638,663,687]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Aspidistra" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pingtangensis">
<emphasis box="[136,313,663,687]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">A. pingtangensis</emphasis>
S.Z. He, W.F. Xu &amp; Q.W. Sun
</taxonomicName>
in 
<bibRefCitation author="He, S. Z. &amp; Xu, W. F. &amp; Wang, Y. Y. &amp; Sun, Q. W." box="[672,893,663,687]" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" pagination="187 - 189" refId="ref1933" refString="He, S. Z., Xu, W. F., Wang, Y. Y. &amp; Sun, Q. W. (2011) A new species of Aspidistra (Ruscaceae) from Guizhou, China. Novon 21 (2): 187 - 189. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.3417 / 2009001" type="journal article" year="2011">
He 
<emphasis box="[710,763,663,687]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">et al.</emphasis>
(2011: 187)
</bibRefCitation>
in perianth with keels externally but strongly differs in the erect stem.
</paragraph>
